<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFE8FFC9A5CDFC6F1B9AFB0C" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFE8FFC9A5CDFC6F1FE0FC11" blockId="24.[136,479,950,977]" box="[136,479,950,977]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFE8FFC9A5CDFC6F1FE0FC11" box="[136,479,950,977]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="4">
9. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFE8FFC9A5E1FC6F1FE5FC11" authority="Adanson (1763: 505)" authorityName="Adanson" authorityPageNumber="505" authorityYear="1763" box="[164,474,950,977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Priva" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE8FFC9A5E1FC6F1EDDFC10" bold="true" box="[164,226,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Priva</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE8FFC9A5ACFC6F1FE5FC11" author="Adanson, M." box="[233,474,950,977]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref32851" refString="Adanson, M. (1763) Familles des Plantes, 2. Vincent, Paris, 640 pp." type="book" year="1763">Adanson (1763: 505)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFE8FFC9A5CDFC271B9AFB0C" blockId="24.[136,1452,1022,1409]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Herbs, monoecious, branches without prickles, not aromatic. Leaves petiolate, glands near to the petiole absent. Inflorescences terminal, simple, racemes spiciform, multiflorous, rachis elongated; bracts membranaceous, green; bracteoles absent. Flowers pedicellate; calyx cylindrical-tubular or campanulate, shorter than the corolla, membranaceous, green, 5-lobed, accrescent and inflated in fruit; corolla zygomorphic, 5-lobed; stamens 4, included, didynamous, superior pair with glandular thickening in the connective, thecae divergent; ovary 2-carpelate, 4-loculate, ovules 1 per locule, stigma 2-lobed. Fruit schizocarp, with 2 mericarps, brown, external surface uncinate or echinate.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFE8FFC9A5F8FB0E1A16FA40" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFE8FFC9A5F8FB0E1A16FA40" blockId="24.[136,1452,1022,1409]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFE8FFC9A5F8FB0E1EC4FB30" authorityName="Adanson" authorityYear="1763" box="[189,251,1239,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Priva" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE8FFC9A5F8FB0E1EC4FB30" box="[189,251,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Priva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFE8FFC9A48AFB0F1CC8FB30" authority="(Marx et al. 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Marx" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[463,759,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Priveae">
Priveae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE8FFC9A777FB0F1CD0FB30" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[562,751,1238,1264]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE8FFC9A732FB0E1C90FB30" box="[631,687,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and presents approximately 20 species distributed throughout the Neotropical Region, of which two are endemic to South America (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE8FFC9A6FDFB231A61FAD4" author="Kobuski, C. E." box="[952,1118,1274,1300]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref35000" refString="Kobuski, C. E. (1926) A revision of the genus Priva. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 13: 1 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2394054" type="journal article" year="1926">Kobuski 1926</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE8FFC9A12EFB231B1DFAD4" author="Moldenke, H. N." box="[1131,1314,1274,1300]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref35784" refString="Moldenke, H. N. (1936) A monograph of the genus Priva. Repertorium novarum specierum regni vegetabilis 41: 1 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19360410103" type="journal article" year="1936">Moldenke 1936</bibRefCitation>
, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE8FFC9A0D2FB221F37FAF8" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al. in press</emphasis>
). The genus is characterized by the pedicellate flowers; 5-lobed calyx, accrescent and inflated in fruit, densely covered by trichomes that aid the fruit dispersal (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE8FFC9A64FFA9B1DFEFA9D" author="Moldenke, H. N." box="[778,961,1346,1373]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref35784" refString="Moldenke, H. N. (1936) A monograph of the genus Priva. Repertorium novarum specierum regni vegetabilis 41: 1 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19360410103" type="journal article" year="1936">Moldenke 1936</bibRefCitation>
). Two species occur in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFE8FFC9A183FA9B1B32FA9C" box="[1222,1293,1346,1372]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, of which one is endemic (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE8FFC9A44AFABF1C73FA41" author="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G." box="[271,588,1382,1409]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref33451" refString="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G. (2020 b) Priva in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 119901 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">Cardoso &amp; Salimena 2020b</bibRefCitation>
). Both species are found in 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFE8FFC9A6C7FABF1A1AFA40" box="[898,1061,1382,1408]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
